title: Follow live: Chiefs, Bills trading scores with spot in Super Bowl on the line
author: Brooke Pryor

title: Eagles reach Super Bowl behind Barkley, Hurts
description: Saquon Barkley and Jalen Hurts each rushed for three touchdowns to carry the Eagles past the Commanders and to a berth in the Super Bowl.

title: Amorim says he'd rather pick 63-year-old coach over Rashford
description: Manchester United boss Ruben Amorim suggests he'd rather give a place on the bench to his 63-year-old goalkeeping coach over Marcus Rashford because of effort.

title: Postecoglou unsure on future - but why do many Spurs fans blame Levy?
description: Tottenham are on a seven-match winless run in the Premier League but it is chairman Daniel Levy - not manager Ange Postecoglou - that is bearing the brunt of supporters' anger.

title: Eagles put up 55 points in rout of Commanders to reach Super Bowl
description: Jalen Hurts and Saquon Barkley each had three rushing touchdowns as the Philadelphia Eagles hammered the Washington Commanders 55-23 to book a Super Bowl spot for the second time in three seasons.

title: Pep says Khusanov will learn from tough debut - was starting him a mistake?
description: Pep Guardiola has backed Man City newcomer Abdukodir Khusanov to learn from a difficult debut against Chelsea, in which he was at fault for the Blues' third-minute opener, after Sky Sports pundit Jamie Redknapp said it was a mistake to start the defender.

title: Live updates: Allen and Bills look to dethrone Mahomes and Chiefs
description: Buffalo is still pushing for its breakthrough moment, but Kansas City stands in the way on the path to the Super Bowl. Will Josh Allen & Co. finally slay the AFC's giants?

title: Xavier Worthy somehow wrestled a pass away from a Bills defender for a controversial catch
description: Did either player catch Patrick Mahomes' pass before it hit the ground?
author: Yahoo Sports
